00:45:06.740 --> 00:45:09.800 align:middle line:84%
>> A gene is a blueprint--
that's basically what it is--

00:45:09.800 --> 00:45:12.330 align:middle line:90%
to make a protein molecule.

00:45:12.330 --> 00:45:14.860 align:middle line:84%
And the proteins-- there
are over 100,000 of them--

00:45:14.860 --> 00:45:16.415 align:middle line:84%
are the building
blocks that give us

00:45:16.415 --> 00:45:19.700 align:middle line:84%
our biology, our
structure, our behavior.

00:45:19.700 --> 00:45:21.890 align:middle line:84%
So the issue is, we talk
about gene blueprints.

00:45:21.890 --> 00:45:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And up until the last
10 years, a blueprint

00:45:24.680 --> 00:45:26.930 align:middle line:84%
was a hardwired
piece of information

00:45:26.930 --> 00:45:29.030 align:middle line:90%
to make a particular protein.

00:45:29.030 --> 00:45:31.340 align:middle line:84%
The new science is
just mind boggling,

00:45:31.340 --> 00:45:34.590 align:middle line:84%
because it reveals that
through epigenetic mechanisms,

00:45:34.590 --> 00:45:36.770 align:middle line:84%
through the influence of
the environment on reading

00:45:36.770 --> 00:45:40.580 align:middle line:84%
the genes, epigenetic
mechanisms can produce over

00:45:40.580 --> 00:45:45.519 align:middle line:84%
30,000 different variations
from every gene blueprint.

00:45:45.519 --> 00:45:47.060 align:middle line:84%
And all of the
sudden, when you start

00:45:47.060 --> 00:45:49.070 align:middle line:84%
to recognize that,
you realize, we

00:45:49.070 --> 00:45:51.620 align:middle line:84%
have potentials that
are totally unlimited.

00:45:51.620 --> 00:45:54.200 align:middle line:84%
And this is a great
change from a belief

00:45:54.200 --> 00:45:56.510 align:middle line:90%
that genes were deterministic.

00:45:56.510 --> 00:45:58.670 align:middle line:90%
Now genes are potentials.

00:45:58.670 --> 00:46:01.130 align:middle line:10%
>> If you just look at
the molecular level,

00:46:01.130 --> 00:46:04.280 align:middle line:10%
the Human Genome Project has
revealed that we have about

00:46:04.280 --> 00:46:08.840 align:middle line:10%
25,000 genes, far fewer than
they originally expected.

00:46:08.840 --> 00:46:11.210 align:middle line:84%
The Chimpanzee Genome
Project has now

00:46:11.210 --> 00:46:14.150 align:middle line:84%
sequenced the entire
chimpanzee genome,

00:46:14.150 --> 00:46:16.756 align:middle line:84%
and their genome is
virtually the same as ours.

00:46:16.756 --> 00:46:18.380 align:middle line:84%
They've got the same
kinds of proteins,

00:46:18.380 --> 00:46:19.830 align:middle line:90%
the same kind of genes.

00:46:19.830 --> 00:46:21.920 align:middle line:84%
You can hardly tell
the difference.

00:46:21.920 --> 00:46:23.690 align:middle line:84%
Yet there's an
obvious difference.

00:46:23.690 --> 00:46:27.320 align:middle line:84%
And if you can't explain it in
terms of genes, what can you

00:46:27.320 --> 00:46:28.640 align:middle line:90%
explain it in terms of?

00:46:28.640 --> 00:46:32.720 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is, I think,
morphogenetic fields.

00:46:32.720 --> 00:46:36.050 align:middle line:84%
Just as you can build
two different buildings

00:46:36.050 --> 00:46:38.180 align:middle line:84%
with the same bricks
and cement, if you

00:46:38.180 --> 00:46:41.840 align:middle line:84%
have two different plans, you
can build different organisms

00:46:41.840 --> 00:46:44.900 align:middle line:84%
with different fields, even
if the constituent molecules

00:46:44.900 --> 00:46:49.610 align:middle line:84%
are very similar, as they are
in humans and chimpanzees.

00:46:49.610 --> 00:46:51.950 align:middle line:84%
>> The DNA is like
a library book.

00:46:51.950 --> 00:46:55.190 align:middle line:10%
These are all the possible
proteins from earthworms

00:46:55.190 --> 00:46:57.020 align:middle line:10%
right up to us.

00:46:57.020 --> 00:46:59.810 align:middle line:10%
it's all the same
library, but you've

00:46:59.810 --> 00:47:04.070 align:middle line:10%
got to know which book to
take out of the library.

00:47:04.070 --> 00:47:06.480 align:middle line:84%
This is the big
problem in genetics

00:47:06.480 --> 00:47:11.040 align:middle line:84%
itself, is trying to
explain how the body knows

00:47:11.040 --> 00:47:14.790 align:middle line:84%
which book to take out
of the genetic library.

00:47:14.790 --> 00:47:18.270 align:middle line:84%
And we think the
body field is what

00:47:18.270 --> 00:47:21.840 align:middle line:84%
decides which piece
of information

00:47:21.840 --> 00:47:23.060 align:middle line:90%
is taken from the DNA.

00:47:23.060 --> 00:47:26.090 align:middle line:90%


00:47:26.090 --> 00:47:28.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Many cultures of the past
have explored the energetic

00:47:28.970 --> 00:47:30.830 align:middle line:90%
system of the body.

00:47:30.830 --> 00:47:33.410 align:middle line:84%
Today researchers
theorize that the body

00:47:33.410 --> 00:47:37.760 align:middle line:84%
does have a field of energy
known as the morphogenic field,

00:47:37.760 --> 00:47:39.560 align:middle line:90%
or the body field.

00:47:39.560 --> 00:47:42.650 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a hierarchy of
fields organizing our bodies.

00:47:42.650 --> 00:47:44.150 align:middle line:84%
There's the field
of the whole body.

00:47:44.150 --> 00:47:45.920 align:middle line:84%
There's the fields of
the organs, and then

00:47:45.920 --> 00:47:47.378 align:middle line:84%
the fields of the
tissues, and then

00:47:47.378 --> 00:47:49.790 align:middle line:84%
the fields of the
cells within those.

00:47:49.790 --> 00:47:53.480 align:middle line:84%
Fields of our own body is
within and around the body.

00:47:53.480 --> 00:47:54.710 align:middle line:90%
There's an overall field.

00:47:54.710 --> 00:47:57.050 align:middle line:84%
And then there's
subsidiary fields,

00:47:57.050 --> 00:48:02.421 align:middle line:84%
sort of modular fields for arms,
legs, and the different organs.

00:48:02.421 --> 00:48:06.670 align:middle line:84%
The advantage of fields is that
they're intrinsically holistic.

00:48:06.670 --> 00:48:08.470 align:middle line:90%
All fields are holistic.

00:48:08.470 --> 00:48:10.000 align:middle line:90%
The gravitational field is.

00:48:10.000 --> 00:48:12.310 align:middle line:90%
You can't slice a bit out of it.

00:48:12.310 --> 00:48:15.160 align:middle line:84%
If you cut a flatworm
into 10 different pieces,

00:48:15.160 --> 00:48:18.380 align:middle line:84%
each part can grow
into a new worm.

00:48:18.380 --> 00:48:20.510 align:middle line:90%
Now how is that possible?

00:48:20.510 --> 00:48:23.210 align:middle line:84%
If it was a machine,
that wouldn't happen.

00:48:23.210 --> 00:48:27.470 align:middle line:84%
If you cut up a machine, all
you get is a broken machine.

00:48:27.470 --> 00:48:31.610 align:middle line:84%
But if you cut up a magnet,
a field system, then however

00:48:31.610 --> 00:48:33.590 align:middle line:84%
many little bits of
magnet you produce,

00:48:33.590 --> 00:48:36.800 align:middle line:84%
each has a complete
magnetic field.

00:48:36.800 --> 00:48:40.280 align:middle line:84%
And it was this analogy
with magnetic fields

00:48:40.280 --> 00:48:43.340 align:middle line:84%
that lead developmental
biologists to suggest

00:48:43.340 --> 00:48:46.040 align:middle line:84%
the idea of morphogenetic
fields in the first place,

00:48:46.040 --> 00:48:48.920 align:middle line:84%
and this was way
back in the 1920s.

00:48:48.920 --> 00:48:51.110 align:middle line:84%
And this field is
now a crucial concept

00:48:51.110 --> 00:48:53.090 align:middle line:90%
in developmental biology.

00:48:53.090 --> 00:48:57.320 align:middle line:84%
You can't really understand how
organisms develop without it.

00:48:57.320 --> 00:49:00.830 align:middle line:84%
>> All humans begin life
as a single cell that grows

00:49:00.830 --> 00:49:04.940 align:middle line:84%
and divides, developing into
the various organs and limbs

00:49:04.940 --> 00:49:06.340 align:middle line:90%
of our bodies.

00:49:06.340 --> 00:49:08.420 align:middle line:84%
How these cells
know what to become

00:49:08.420 --> 00:49:11.390 align:middle line:84%
has baffled scientists
and led to the idea

00:49:11.390 --> 00:49:15.260 align:middle line:90%
of controlled fields in biology.

00:49:15.260 --> 00:49:19.130 align:middle line:10%
>> We've already found that
there are different parts

00:49:19.130 --> 00:49:22.610 align:middle line:10%
of the body field, some of
which relate to the muscles

00:49:22.610 --> 00:49:23.956 align:middle line:10%
and connective tissue.

00:49:23.956 --> 00:49:25.580 align:middle line:84%
There's another part
of the body field

00:49:25.580 --> 00:49:29.390 align:middle line:84%
that relates to the
brain and nervous system.

00:49:29.390 --> 00:49:32.960 align:middle line:84%
Yet another one for the
morphic field, which connects

00:49:32.960 --> 00:49:38.150 align:middle line:84%
back to the DNA and the genetic
information of your body.

00:49:38.150 --> 00:49:40.890 align:middle line:10%
So it links up with
medicine in many places,

00:49:40.890 --> 00:49:42.770 align:middle line:10%
so it's not different
from medicine.

00:49:42.770 --> 00:49:46.790 align:middle line:10%
It's just going a little
bit further conceptually.

00:49:46.790 --> 00:49:49.640 align:middle line:84%
>> These energetic fields
may provide the information

00:49:49.640 --> 00:49:53.000 align:middle line:84%
necessary for
controlling the body.

00:49:53.000 --> 00:49:56.870 align:middle line:84%
>> How does the body know
to maintain its temperature

00:49:56.870 --> 00:49:59.450 align:middle line:90%
at a particular temperature?

00:49:59.450 --> 00:50:02.420 align:middle line:84%
What decides or
who decides what is

00:50:02.420 --> 00:50:07.500 align:middle line:84%
going to be the correct blood
pressure for that person?

00:50:07.500 --> 00:50:08.340 align:middle line:90%
Nobody knows.

00:50:08.340 --> 00:50:12.060 align:middle line:84%
And we're saying
as a holistic idea,

00:50:12.060 --> 00:50:16.410 align:middle line:84%
the body field decides
to turn all the knobs.

00:50:16.410 --> 00:50:19.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Informational health care
means that if we take the ideas

00:50:19.560 --> 00:50:23.190 align:middle line:84%
of epigenetics, we're actually
able to take the information

00:50:23.190 --> 00:50:25.830 align:middle line:84%
from your original blueprint
of how your body works when

00:50:25.830 --> 00:50:29.010 align:middle line:84%
it's working perfectly,
imprint that information back

00:50:29.010 --> 00:50:30.020 align:middle line:90%
into the body.

00:50:30.020 --> 00:50:32.850 align:middle line:84%
And as you do that, the body
starts to correct itself

00:50:32.850 --> 00:50:36.480 align:middle line:84%
and goes back towards that
original healthy blueprint.

00:50:36.480 --> 00:50:38.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Morphogenetic fields,
or more generally,

00:50:38.640 --> 00:50:42.960 align:middle line:84%
fields of information, yes, are
control systems over and above

00:50:42.960 --> 00:50:47.740 align:middle line:84%
the molecular level or
the biochemical level.

00:50:47.740 --> 00:50:49.710 align:middle line:84%
They're systems that
organize the body.

00:50:49.710 --> 00:50:52.470 align:middle line:84%
They organize the
developing organism.

00:50:52.470 --> 00:50:54.165 align:middle line:90%
Plants have them too.

00:50:54.165 --> 00:50:56.790 align:middle line:90%
All animals have them.

00:50:56.790 --> 00:50:58.830 align:middle line:84%
They maintain the
form of the body.

00:50:58.830 --> 00:51:02.250 align:middle line:84%
They help bodies to recover
from disease or damage.

00:51:02.250 --> 00:51:04.990 align:middle line:84%
They underlie
regeneration, for example.

00:51:04.990 --> 00:51:08.700 align:middle line:84%
And I think that we really need
a field-based model of the body

00:51:08.700 --> 00:51:10.530 align:middle line:84%
if we're ever going to
be able to integrate

00:51:10.530 --> 00:51:12.360 align:middle line:84%
different forms of
healing or medicine

00:51:12.360 --> 00:51:16.890 align:middle line:90%
into a coherent understanding.

00:51:16.890 --> 00:51:19.140 align:middle line:84%
>> The body field is
an energetic field,

00:51:19.140 --> 00:51:22.020 align:middle line:84%
filled with patterns
of information.

00:51:22.020 --> 00:51:24.270 align:middle line:84%
All of the organs in
our bodies generate

00:51:24.270 --> 00:51:26.790 align:middle line:90%
their own specific fields.

00:51:26.790 --> 00:51:30.510 align:middle line:84%
One organ in particular seems
to generate significant fields

00:51:30.510 --> 00:51:34.130 align:middle line:90%
which affect the entire body.

00:51:34.130 --> 00:51:36.300 align:middle line:84%
>> The heart is the
emperor in the system.

00:51:36.300 --> 00:51:39.630 align:middle line:84%
The liver and all the
organs have other tasks,

00:51:39.630 --> 00:51:42.520 align:middle line:90%
but the heart is overruling all.

00:51:42.520 --> 00:51:45.220 align:middle line:10%
>> There's a concept in
energy medicine called energy

00:51:45.220 --> 00:51:51.460 align:middle line:10%
cardiology that says that these
signals produced by the heart

00:51:51.460 --> 00:51:55.150 align:middle line:10%
are all of regulatory
importance.

00:51:55.150 --> 00:52:00.050 align:middle line:84%
The heart is constantly emitting
sound, pressure waves, heat,

00:52:00.050 --> 00:52:05.230 align:middle line:84%
light, electrical, magnetic,
and electromagnetic signals.

00:52:05.230 --> 00:52:09.730 align:middle line:84%
>> All of the cells in the body
are receiving these different

00:52:09.730 --> 00:52:12.820 align:middle line:84%
kinds of signals
at different times,

00:52:12.820 --> 00:52:16.120 align:middle line:84%
because they travel at
different velocities through

00:52:16.120 --> 00:52:17.950 align:middle line:90%
the circulatory system.

00:52:17.950 --> 00:52:21.160 align:middle line:10%
>> The heart generates by
far the largest rhythmic

00:52:21.160 --> 00:52:23.682 align:middle line:10%
electromagnetic
signal in the body.

00:52:23.682 --> 00:52:29.100 align:middle line:84%
If you look at this magnetic
field as a carrier wave,

00:52:29.100 --> 00:52:31.770 align:middle line:84%
it's being modulated
with information so as

00:52:31.770 --> 00:52:34.170 align:middle line:90%
to carry away for information.

00:52:34.170 --> 00:52:36.030 align:middle line:84%
And the work in
our lab has shown

00:52:36.030 --> 00:52:38.620 align:middle line:84%
quite clearly that
it's modulated

00:52:38.620 --> 00:52:40.496 align:middle line:90%
with emotional patterns.

00:52:40.496 --> 00:52:44.830 align:middle line:84%
In other words, if we're feeling
angry or frustrated, irritated,

00:52:44.830 --> 00:52:47.650 align:middle line:84%
the information
that's been imprinted

00:52:47.650 --> 00:52:50.800 align:middle line:84%
on that magnetic field
is very different

00:52:50.800 --> 00:52:53.500 align:middle line:84%
than if we're feeling
care or love or compassion

00:52:53.500 --> 00:52:55.270 align:middle line:90%
towards that person.

00:52:55.270 --> 00:52:58.450 align:middle line:10%
>> The heart has been found to
have rhythmic beating patterns

00:52:58.450 --> 00:53:01.730 align:middle line:10%
that can be incoherent
or coherent.

00:53:01.730 --> 00:53:04.820 align:middle line:10%
These patterns are closely
linked to our emotions

00:53:04.820 --> 00:53:06.590 align:middle line:10%
and how we feel.

00:53:06.590 --> 00:53:10.700 align:middle line:10%
>> When the heart's rhythmic
beating pattern is smooth

00:53:10.700 --> 00:53:13.430 align:middle line:10%
and ordered, it's called
a coherent rhythm.

00:53:13.430 --> 00:53:18.080 align:middle line:84%
And that coherent rhythm
entrains or synchronizes

00:53:18.080 --> 00:53:19.790 align:middle line:84%
the brain rhythm,
the nervous system.

00:53:19.790 --> 00:53:23.210 align:middle line:84%
The bodily organs and
glands all dance in harmony

00:53:23.210 --> 00:53:25.700 align:middle line:90%
to that heart coherent rhythm.

00:53:25.700 --> 00:53:28.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Positive emotions, what
we tend to call positive--

00:53:28.550 --> 00:53:32.780 align:middle line:84%
things like love, appreciation,
care, forgiveness, gratitude--

00:53:32.780 --> 00:53:35.430 align:middle line:84%
all lead to a very different
kind of heart pattern

00:53:35.430 --> 00:53:36.860 align:middle line:90%
than negative things.

00:53:36.860 --> 00:53:40.150 align:middle line:84%
Like if we're feeling anger
or irritation, anxiety,

00:53:40.150 --> 00:53:43.010 align:middle line:84%
those create what are
called incoherent rhythms

00:53:43.010 --> 00:53:44.760 align:middle line:90%
or disordered patterns.

00:53:44.760 --> 00:53:46.760 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, we
have the positive feelings

00:53:46.760 --> 00:53:50.939 align:middle line:84%
when we're just appreciating the
sunset and how beautiful it is.

00:53:50.939 --> 00:53:53.480 align:middle line:84%
Our hearts beating out this--
what we call a coherent rhythm.

00:53:53.480 --> 00:53:57.080 align:middle line:84%
It's a sign wave-like
pattern that the heart

00:53:57.080 --> 00:54:00.900 align:middle line:90%
is sending to the brain.

00:54:00.900 --> 00:54:03.480 align:middle line:84%
>> And we call it heart
coherence, because in research,

00:54:03.480 --> 00:54:06.230 align:middle line:84%
we find that the heart has to
get into this synchronized,

00:54:06.230 --> 00:54:10.520 align:middle line:84%
coherent, rhythmic pattern
of heart rate in order

00:54:10.520 --> 00:54:13.190 align:middle line:84%
for the rest of the brain and
the nervous system and body

00:54:13.190 --> 00:54:17.330 align:middle line:84%
to entrain and synchronize
to that powerful rhythm.

00:54:17.330 --> 00:54:19.230 align:middle line:90%
So it starts with the heart.

00:54:19.230 --> 00:54:22.010 align:middle line:84%
>> When we feel the pulse, what
we're feeling is the pressure

00:54:22.010 --> 00:54:23.930 align:middle line:84%
wave created by
the beating heart.

00:54:23.930 --> 00:54:25.430 align:middle line:84%
It's not actually
the flow of blood.

00:54:25.430 --> 00:54:27.109 align:middle line:90%
It's the pressure wave.

00:54:27.109 --> 00:54:29.150 align:middle line:84%
So every time the heart
beats, that pressure wave

00:54:29.150 --> 00:54:31.840 align:middle line:84%
goes to the brain and
throughout the body.

00:54:31.840 --> 00:54:33.860 align:middle line:84%
And if we look at
the brain level,

00:54:33.860 --> 00:54:36.662 align:middle line:84%
that pressure wave
synchronizes all the neurons.

00:54:36.662 --> 00:54:38.120 align:middle line:84%
Like, the brain
would be in trouble

00:54:38.120 --> 00:54:41.170 align:middle line:84%
if it didn't have that
synchronizing signal

00:54:41.170 --> 00:54:43.880 align:middle line:84%
to kind of give us a global
synchronizing effect.

00:54:43.880 --> 00:54:47.090 align:middle line:84%
>> When someone is in coherence,
you can often feel their love

00:54:47.090 --> 00:54:50.420 align:middle line:84%
or their compassion or
their gratitude radiating.

00:54:50.420 --> 00:54:53.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Coherence is the optimal
physiological state that

00:54:53.180 --> 00:54:56.870 align:middle line:84%
underlies learning and
performance and facilitating

00:54:56.870 --> 00:55:01.190 align:middle line:84%
the body's natural
regenerative processes.

00:55:01.190 --> 00:55:04.230 align:middle line:84%
>> The heart has its own
intrinsic nervous system,

00:55:04.230 --> 00:55:09.150 align:middle line:84%
which can sense, feel, remember,
and process information

00:55:09.150 --> 00:55:12.110 align:middle line:84%
that's independent
from the brain.

00:55:12.110 --> 00:55:16.490 align:middle line:84%
>> We always think of the
information input system

00:55:16.490 --> 00:55:19.970 align:middle line:90%
as being entirely in the brain.

00:55:19.970 --> 00:55:22.130 align:middle line:84%
But we're now
discovering information

00:55:22.130 --> 00:55:25.640 align:middle line:84%
that the heart receives
information first, and then

00:55:25.640 --> 00:55:28.360 align:middle line:90%
relays it to the brain.

00:55:28.360 --> 00:55:31.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Studies have shown that
the heart responds faster than

00:55:31.360 --> 00:55:34.480 align:middle line:84%
the brain to
outside stimulation.

00:55:34.480 --> 00:55:38.170 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the more recent
studies we did in our labs was

00:55:38.170 --> 00:55:41.136 align:middle line:84%
looking at what we ended up
titling the electrophysiology

00:55:41.136 --> 00:55:42.580 align:middle line:90%
of intuition.

00:55:42.580 --> 00:55:45.670 align:middle line:84%
And there was some previous
research that had been done,

00:55:45.670 --> 00:55:48.100 align:middle line:84%
showing that the
body would respond

00:55:48.100 --> 00:55:51.480 align:middle line:84%
in a way that would
predict a future event

00:55:51.480 --> 00:55:53.440 align:middle line:84%
if the future event
was emotionally

00:55:53.440 --> 00:55:56.330 align:middle line:84%
significant and
relevant to the person.

00:55:56.330 --> 00:55:59.030 align:middle line:84%
